@startuml
title EventMate External Event Data Subsystem - Static Structure

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
left to right direction

interface EventDataProvider <<provider contract>> {
    +retrieveEvents(classification): Event[]
}

class TicketmasterServices <<external API adapter>> {
    +fetchTicketmasterEvents(classification): Event[]
}

class MockEventProvider <<fallback provider; planned>> {
    +retrieveEvents(classification): Event[]
    +loadMockEvents(): Event[]
}

class EventSyncService <<service>> {
    +handleSync(classifications)
    -selectProvider(): EventDataProvider
}

class EventNormalizer <<normalizer>> {
    +normalizeEvent(rawEvent, canonicalKey)
}

class CanonicalKeyGenerator <<utility>> {
    +generateCanonicalKey(rawEvent): String
}

class DescriptionGenerator <<utility>> {
    +generateDescription(rawEvent): String
}

class EventModel <<model>> {
    +insert(event)
    +findByCanonicalKey(key)
    +insertOccurrence(eventId, time)
}

class VenueModel <<model>> {
    +upsert(venue)
}

class PostgreSQL <<database>>

TicketmasterServices ..|> EventDataProvider
MockEventProvider ..|> EventDataProvider
EventSyncService --> EventDataProvider : selects
EventSyncService --> CanonicalKeyGenerator
EventSyncService --> EventNormalizer
EventNormalizer --> DescriptionGenerator
EventSyncService --> EventModel
EventSyncService --> VenueModel
EventModel --> PostgreSQL
VenueModel --> PostgreSQL

note bottom of MockEventProvider
Used when Ticketmaster is disabled, unavailable,
rate-limited, or returns invalid data. Both providers
must produce the same normalized Event format.
end note

note bottom of EventSyncService
eventsServices.js currently contains handleSync().
The provider-selection operation represents the
fallback behavior required by the revised design.
end note

@enduml
